    "This can be done, for example, by (i) arranging code into logical sections like functions, classes and modules; (ii) refactoring code by suggesting better naming conventions, eliminating code duplication, and improving overall code readability; (iii) suggesting alternative algorithms or data structures that may improve efficiency and performance of the code; or (iv) writing clearer code annotations.",
    "An LLM can also aid in debugging and error detection (Box 5).",
    "Yet, suggestions from LLMs may not necessarily provide the most efficient code or follow established best practices in the environmental factors1.",
    "Moreover, they identify eight distinct clusters of traits that capture the full dimensionality of trait space.",
    "These clusters reflect different aspects of tree form and function such as drought tolerance, shade tolerance, dispersal ability and nutrient cycling."
